## DeepMergeTuple type

Merge two tuples, values of the second array will assign values of the array type.

**Signature:**

```typescript
export type DeepMergeTuple<
  A extends readonly unknown[],
  B extends readonly unknown[],
> = If<
  IsReadonlyArray<B>,
  readonly [...InternalDeepMergeTupleValue<A, B>, ...Slice<A, B['length']>],
  [...InternalDeepMergeTupleValue<A, B>, ...Slice<A, B['length']>]
>
```
**References:** [If](./types-kit.if.md)<!-- -->, [IsReadonlyArray](./types-kit.isreadonlyarray.md)<!-- -->, [InternalDeepMergeTupleValue](./types-kit.internaldeepmergetuplevalue.md)<!-- -->, [Slice](./types-kit.slice.md)

## Example


```ts
    type Foo = [{ a: 1 }, 2, 3]
    type Bar = [{ b: 2 }, 5]
    // Expect: [{ a: 1, b: 2 }, 5, 3]
    type MergedTuple = DeepMergeTuple<Foo, Bar>
```
